pxchat.net.protocol.frames
Class VersionFrame

java.lang.Object
  pxchat.net.protocol.frames.Frame
      pxchat.net.protocol.frames.VersionFrame
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class VersionFrame
extends Frame

This frame is used to send the version of the client software to the server. Should the version not be compatible, the connection is closed.

Author:
Robert Waury

isCompatible

public boolean isCompatible(VersionFrame ver)
Checks whether the version is compatible with the specified version. A difference in the minor number does not make two versions incompatible, a difference in the major numbers does.

Parameters:
ver - The version to check compatibility with.
Returns:
true if the versions are compatible, false else
